## Monitoring & Logging

### Application Monitoring

<!-- {{#if tauri}} -->
**Desktop App Logs**:
- Location: `~/.{{projectName}}/logs/`
- Rotation: Daily, keep 7 days
- Level: Info in production, Debug in development

**Crash Reporting**:
```rust
// Setup crash reporter
use tauri::plugin::sentry;

tauri::Builder::default()
    .plugin(sentry::init())
    .run(tauri::generate_context!())
    .expect("error while running tauri application");
```
<!-- {{/if}} -->

<!-- {{#if nextjs-aws}} -->
**CloudWatch Dashboards**:
- API response times
- Lambda error rates
- Database connections
- CloudFront cache hit ratio

**Logs**:
- Lambda logs: CloudWatch Logs
- Application logs: CloudWatch Logs Insights
- Access logs: S3 (CloudFront)

**Alerting**:
```typescript
// infrastructure/lib/monitoring-stack.ts
const alarm = new cloudwatch.Alarm(this, 'ApiErrorAlarm', {
  metric: apiFunction.metricErrors(),
  threshold: 10,
  evaluationPeriods: 2,
  alarmDescription: 'Alert when API errors exceed 10 in 10 minutes',
});

alarm.addAlarmAction(new sns_actions.SnsAction(alertTopic));
```
