## Rollback Procedures

### Quick Rollback

<!-- {{#if tauri}} -->
**Desktop App**:
Users can download previous version from GitHub Releases:
```
https://github.com/{{organization}}/{{projectName}}/releases/tag/v1.0.0
```

**Auto-updater** prevents forced updates - users can skip.
<!-- {{/if}} -->

<!-- {{#if nextjs-aws}} -->
**Web App** (CDK):
```bash
# Revert to previous stack version
cdk deploy --rollback

# Or deploy specific version
git checkout v1.0.0
cd infrastructure
cdk deploy --all
```

**Database Rollback**:
```bash
# Run down migration
{{packageManager}} run db:migrate:down
```

**Emergency**: Route traffic to previous CloudFront distribution
<!-- {{/if}} -->

### Rollback Decision Tree

```
Issue detected
    ├─ Affects < 1% users → Monitor, fix in next release
    ├─ Affects 1-10% users → Hotfix and deploy
    └─ Affects > 10% users → Immediate rollback
```

